5.       Does the platform use any caching schemes to fast serve its clients?
Yes

In Fiddler-managed deployments, we use AWS ElastiCache. We use Redis in three ways:
• As a results backend for asynchronous tasks;
• As a cache for heavily accessed data entities;
• Ingestion uses Redis Stream constructs (write-ahead logs) to buffer data;

